            <example>
                <statement>
                    <p>
                        Evaluate the expression <m>5^2</m>.
                    </p>
                </statement>
                <solution>
                    <p>
                       First identify the Base and Exponent:
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        In <m>5^2</m>, the base is <m>5</m>, and the exponent is <m>2</m>.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        According to the definition of exponents, <m>5^2</m> means <m>5</m> multiplied by itself <m>2</m> times.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Next, multiply the base by itself: <m>5 \times 5</m>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Calculating the Result: <m>5 \times 5 25</m>
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        Therefore, the value of <m>5^2</m> is <m>25</m>.
                    </p>
                </solution>
            </example>
            
